            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>
              The Occultation Research Group is dedicated to advancing our understanding of trans-Neptunian objects (TNOs) 
              and other small bodies in the outer solar system through high-precision stellar occultation observations. 
              Our research contributes to fundamental questions about the formation and evolution of our solar system.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Research Focus</h2>
            <p>Our primary research areas include:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Stellar Occultations:</strong> High-precision observations of TNOs passing in front of background stars</li>
              <li><strong>Size and Shape Determination:</strong> Characterizing the physical properties of small solar system bodies</li>
              <li><strong>Orbital Dynamics:</strong> Improving our understanding of TNO orbital evolution and distribution</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2>Collaboration</h2>
            <p>
              We work closely with amateur astronomers, professional observatories, and international research groups 
              to coordinate observation campagins and share data. 
            </p>
